# .claudeignore — paths Claude Code should not scan or read.
#
# EFFECTIVENESS NOTE: Claude Code's search (ripgrep-based Grep/Glob) honors .gitignore
# automatically, so .gitignore is what actually reduces scanning. This file documents intent
# and is honored by tooling that supports it. For a hard read-block, add Read(deny) rules in
# .claude/settings.local.json. Keep this roughly in sync with .gitignore.

# --- Generated runtime output (machine-written, not source) ---
corpus/inputs.json            # generated input corpus, regenerated on every run
corpus/crashes.json           # generated (deduplicated) crash log
synthedge_findings.py         # generated pytest reproducers
examples/synthedge_findings.py
# (examples/corpus/*.json is a small committed showcase the README cites — intentionally NOT ignored)

# --- Python build / cache artifacts ---
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Launch marketing copy (not technical) ---
docs/show_hn.md
docs/reddit_post.md
docs/launch_checklist.md

# --- Local Claude / editor / VCS / OS ---
.claude/worktrees/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Logs / temp ---
*.log
*.tmp
tmp/
.cache/
